Overview: In November 2021 Portugal exported €6.01B and imported €8.11B, resulting in a negative trade balance of €2.1B. Between November 2020 and November 2021 the exports of Portugal have increased by €815M (15.7%) from €5.19B to €6.01B, while imports increased by €1.99B (32.6%) from €6.11B to €8.11B.
Exports: The top exports of Portugal are Cars ($4.73B), Vehicle Parts ($3.29B), Refined Petroleum ($2.23B), Leather Footwear ($1.84B), and Uncoated Paper ($1.26B), exporting mostly to Spain ($15.4B), France ($8.49B), Germany ($8.06B), United Kingdom ($4.33B), and United States ($3.58B).
In: 2019, Portugal was the world's biggest importer of Raw Cork ($131M)and Debacked Cork ($21.1M)
Imports: The top imports of Portugal are Cars ($5.11B), Crude Petroleum ($4.71B), Planes, Helicopters, and/or Spacecraft ($3.34B), Vehicle Parts ($3.03B), and Packaged Medicaments ($2.15B), importing mostly from Spain ($25.8B), Germany ($11.7B), France ($8.3B), Italy ($4.8B), and Netherlands ($4.26B).
Location: Portugal borders Spain by land and Morocco by sea.
Trade: In November 2021, the top exports of Portugal were Vehicles; other than railway or tramway... (€876M), Electrical machinery and equipment and parts... (€471M), Nuclear reactors, boilers, machinery and mechanical... (€379M), Plastics and articles thereof (€343M), and Mineral fuels, mineral oils and products... (€228M). In November 2021 the top imports of Portugal were Mineral fuels, mineral oils and products... (€1.02B), Electrical machinery and equipment and parts... (€831M), Vehicles; other than railway or tramway... (€818M), Nuclear reactors, boilers, machinery and mechanical... (€736M), and Plastics and articles thereof (€399M).
Destinations: In November 2021, Portugal exported mostly to Spain (€1.66B), France (€768M), Germany (€721M), United States (€304M), and United Kingdom (€303M), and imported mostly from Spain (€2.68B), Germany (€954M), France (€546M), China (€502M), and Netherlands (€422M).
Growth: In November 2021, the increase in Portugal's year-by-year exports was explained primarily by an increase in exports to Spain (€312M or 23.2%), Germany (€137M or 23.4%), and France (€98.4M or 14.7%), and product exports increase in Plastics and articles thereof (€88.1M or 34.6%), Iron or steel articles (€55.8M or 39.9%), and Iron and steel (€52.8M or 48.1%). In November 2021, the increase in Portugal's year-by-year imports was explained primarily by an increase in imports from Spain (€581M or 27.7%), China (€276M or 123%), and Brazil (€159M or 243%), and product imports increase in Mineral fuels, mineral oils and products... (€660M or 184%), Iron and steel (€168M or 91.6%), and Electrical machinery and equipment and parts... (€139M or 20%).
